{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I have all my life wondered what \"mind-boggling\" meant."},{"time":6000,"text":"After two days here, I declare myself boggled, and enormously impressed,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and feel that you are one of the great hopes --"},{"time":22000,"text":"not just for American achievement in science and technology,"},{"time":29000,"text":"but for the whole world."},{"time":31000,"text":"I've come, however, on a special mission on behalf of my constituency,"},{"time":39000,"text":"which are the 10-to-the-18th-power -- that's a million trillion --"},{"time":48000,"text":"insects and other small creatures, and to make a plea for them."},{"time":62000,"text":"If we were to wipe out insects alone, just that group alone, on this planet --"},{"time":68000,"text":"which we are trying hard to do --"},{"time":72000,"text":"the rest of life and humanity with it would mostly disappear from the land."},{"time":81000,"text":"And within a few months."},{"time":83000,"text":"Now, how did I come to this particular position of advocacy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"As a little boy, and through my teenage years,"},{"time":95000,"text":"I became increasingly fascinated by the diversity of life."},{"time":98000,"text":"I had a butterfly period, a snake period, a bird period, a fish period, a cave period"},{"time":110000,"text":"and finally and definitively, an ant period."},{"time":114000,"text":"By my college years, I was a devoted myrmecologist,"},{"time":119000,"text":"a specialist on the biology of ants,"},{"time":121000,"text":"but my attention and research continued to make journeys"},{"time":126000,"text":"across the great variety of life on Earth in general --"},{"time":130000,"text":"including all that it means to us as a species, how little we understand it"},{"time":138000,"text":"and how pressing a danger that our activities have created for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"Out of that broader study has emerged a concern and an ambition,"},{"time":150000,"text":"crystallized in the wish that I'm about to make to you."},{"time":155000,"text":"My choice is the culmination of a lifetime commitment"},{"time":160000,"text":"that began with growing up on the Gulf Coast of Alabama, on the Florida peninsula."},{"time":167000,"text":"As far back as I can remember, I was enchanted by the natural beauty of that region"},{"time":176000,"text":"and the almost tropical exuberance of the plants and animals that grow there."},{"time":182000,"text":"One day when I was only seven years old and fishing,"},{"time":186000,"text":"I pulled a \"pinfish,\" they're called, with sharp dorsal spines, up too hard and fast,"},{"time":194000,"text":"and I blinded myself in one eye."},{"time":196000,"text":"I later discovered I was also hard of hearing,"},{"time":199000,"text":"possibly congenitally, in the upper registers."},{"time":202000,"text":"So in planning to be a professional naturalist --"},{"time":207000,"text":"I never considered anything else in my entire life --"},{"time":210000,"text":"I found that I was lousy at bird watching and couldn't track frog calls either."},{"time":218000,"text":"So I turned to the teeming small creatures"},{"time":222000,"text":"that can be held between the thumb and forefinger:"},{"time":227000,"text":"the little things that compose the foundation of our ecosystems,"},{"time":234000,"text":"the little things, as I like to say, who run the world."},{"time":239000,"text":"In so doing, I reached a frontier of biology so strange, so rich,"},{"time":247000,"text":"that it seemed as though it exists on another planet."},{"time":253000,"text":"In fact, we live on a mostly unexplored planet."},{"time":257000,"text":"The great majority of organisms on Earth remain unknown to science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262000,"text":"In the last 30 years, thanks to explorations in remote parts of the world"},{"time":268000,"text":"and advances in technology,"},{"time":270000,"text":"biologists have, for example, added a full one-third of the known frog and other amphibian species,"},{"time":280000,"text":"to bring the current total to 5,400,"},{"time":284000,"text":"and more continue to pour in."},{"time":286000,"text":"Two new kinds of whales have been discovered, along with two new antelopes,"},{"time":292000,"text":"dozens of monkey species and a new kind of elephant --"},{"time":296000,"text":"and even a distinct kind of gorilla."},{"time":299000,"text":"At the extreme opposite end of the size scale, the class of marine bacteria,"},{"time":309000,"text":"the Prochlorococci -- that will be on the final exam --"},{"time":315000,"text":"although discovered only in 1988, are now recognized as likely the most abundant organisms on Earth,"},{"time":324000,"text":"and moreover, responsible for a large part of the photosynthesis that occurs in the ocean."},{"time":331000,"text":"These bacteria were not uncovered sooner"},{"time":335000,"text":"because they are also among the smallest of all Earth's organisms --"},{"time":340000,"text":"so minute that they cannot be seen with conventional optical microscopy."},{"time":346000,"text":"Yet life in the sea may depend on these tiny creatures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350000,"text":"These examples are just the first glimpse of our ignorance of life on this planet."},{"time":355000,"text":"Consider the fungi -- including mushrooms, rusts, molds and many disease-causing organisms."},{"time":362000,"text":"60,000 species are known to science,"},{"time":366000,"text":"but more than 1.5 million have been estimated to exist."},{"time":370000,"text":"Consider the nematode roundworm, the most abundant of all animals."},{"time":376000,"text":"Four out of five animals on Earth are nematode worms --"},{"time":384000,"text":"if all solid materials except nematode worms were to be eliminated,"},{"time":388000,"text":"you could still see the ghostly outline of most of it in nematode worms."},{"time":395000,"text":"About 16,000 species of nematode worms"},{"time":400000,"text":"have been discovered and diagnosed by scientists;"},{"time":403000,"text":"there could be hundreds of thousands of them, even millions, still unknown."},{"time":408000,"text":"This vast domain of hidden biodiversity is increased still further"},{"time":413000,"text":"by the dark matter of the biological world of bacteria,"},{"time":419000,"text":"which within just the last several years"},{"time":425000,"text":"still were known from only about 6,000 species of bacteria worldwide."},{"time":432000,"text":"But that number of bacteria species can be found in one gram of soil,"},{"time":438000,"text":"just a little handful of soil, in the 10 billion bacteria that would be there."},{"time":447000,"text":"It's been estimated that a single ton of soil -- fertile soil --"},{"time":452000,"text":"contains approximately four million species of bacteria, all unknown."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460000,"text":"So the question is: what are they all doing?"},{"time":468000,"text":"The fact is, we don't know."},{"time":471000,"text":"We are living on a planet with a lot of activities, with reference to our living environment,"},{"time":480000,"text":"done by faith and guess alone."},{"time":484000,"text":"Our lives depend upon these creatures."},{"time":488000,"text":"To take an example close to home: there are over 500 species of bacteria now known --"},{"time":496000,"text":"friendly bacteria -- living symbiotically in your mouth and throat"},{"time":501000,"text":"probably necessary to your health for holding off pathogenic bacteria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"At this point I think we have a little impressionistic film"},{"time":512000,"text":"that was made especially for this occasion."},{"time":514000,"text":"And I'd like to show it."},{"time":517000,"text":"Assisted in this by Billie Holiday."},{"time":520000,"text":"(Video)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"And that may be just the beginning!"},{"time":645000,"text":"The viruses, those quasi-organisms among which are the prophages,"},{"time":651000,"text":"the gene weavers that promote the continued evolution in the lives of the bacteria,"},{"time":658000,"text":"are a virtually unknown frontier of modern biology, a world unto themselves."},{"time":667000,"text":"What constitutes a viral species is still unresolved,"},{"time":671000,"text":"although they're obviously of enormous importance to us."},{"time":675000,"text":"But this much we can say: the variety of genes on the planet in viruses"},{"time":681000,"text":"exceeds, or is likely to exceed, that in all of the rest of life combined."},{"time":689000,"text":"Nowadays, in addressing microbial biodiversity,"},{"time":693000,"text":"scientists are like explorers in a rowboat launched onto the Pacific Ocean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699000,"text":"But that is changing rapidly with the aid of new genomic technology."},{"time":704000,"text":"Already it is possible to sequence the entire genetic code of a bacterium in under four hours."},{"time":711000,"text":"Soon we will be in a position to go forth in the field with sequencers on our backs --"},{"time":717000,"text":"to hunt bacteria in tiny crevices of the habitat's surface"},{"time":723000,"text":"in the way you go watching for birds with binoculars."},{"time":727000,"text":"What will we find as we map the living world, as, finally, we get this underway seriously?"},{"time":735000,"text":"As we move past the relatively gigantic mammals, birds, frogs and plants"},{"time":740000,"text":"to the more elusive insects and other small invertebrates and then beyond"},{"time":746000,"text":"to the countless millions of organisms in the invisible living world"},{"time":751000,"text":"enveloped and living within humanity?"},{"time":755000,"text":"Already what were thought to be bacteria for generations"},{"time":761000,"text":"have been found to compose, instead, two great domains of microorganisms:"},{"time":767000,"text":"true bacteria and one-celled organisms the archaea,"},{"time":771000,"text":"which are closer than other bacteria to the eukaryota, the group that we belong to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778000,"text":"Some serious biologists, and I count myself among them,"},{"time":783000,"text":"have begun to wonder that among the enormous and still unknown diversity of microorganisms,"},{"time":792000,"text":"one might -- just might -- find aliens among them."},{"time":797000,"text":"True aliens, stocks that arrived from outer space."},{"time":802000,"text":"They've had billions of years to do it,"},{"time":804000,"text":"but especially during the earliest period of biological evolution on this planet."},{"time":811000,"text":"We do know that some bacterial species that have earthly origin"},{"time":815000,"text":"are capable of almost unimaginable extremes of temperature"},{"time":823000,"text":"and other harsh changes in environment,"},{"time":826000,"text":"including hard radiation strong enough and maintained long enough to crack the Pyrex vessels"},{"time":834000,"text":"around the growing population of bacteria."},{"time":837000,"text":"There may be a temptation to treat the biosphere holistically"},{"time":843000,"text":"and the species that compose it as a great flux of entities"},{"time":849000,"text":"hardly worth distinguishing one from the other."},{"time":853000,"text":"But each of these species, even the tiniest Prochlorococci,"},{"time":858000,"text":"are masterpieces of evolution."},{"time":860000,"text":"Each has persisted for thousands to millions of years."},{"time":866000,"text":"Each is exquisitely adapted to the environment in which it lives,"},{"time":870000,"text":"interlocked with other species to form ecosystems upon which our own lives depend"},{"time":877000,"text":"in ways we have not begun even to imagine."},{"time":881000,"text":"We will destroy these ecosystems and the species composing them"},{"time":885000,"text":"at the peril of our own existence --"},{"time":888000,"text":"and unfortunately we are destroying them with ingenuity and ceaseless energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":897000,"text":"My own epiphany as a conservationist came in 1953, while a Harvard graduate student,"},{"time":907000,"text":"searching for rare ants found in the mountain forests of Cuba,"},{"time":911000,"text":"ants that shine in the sunlight --"},{"time":913000,"text":"metallic green or metallic blue, according to species, and one species, I discovered, metallic gold."},{"time":921000,"text":"I found my magical ants, but only after a tough climb into the mountains"},{"time":926000,"text":"where the last of the native Cuban forests hung on,"},{"time":930000,"text":"and were then -- and still are -- being cut back."},{"time":936000,"text":"I realized then that these species"},{"time":939000,"text":"and a large part of the other unique, marvelous animals and plants on that island --"},{"time":945000,"text":"and this is true of practically every part of the world --"},{"time":950000,"text":"which took millions of years to evolve, are in the process of disappearing forever."},{"time":955000,"text":"And so it is everywhere one looks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960000,"text":"The human juggernaut is permanently eroding Earth's ancient biosphere by a combination of forces"},{"time":968000,"text":"that can be summarized by the acronym \"HIPPO,\" the animal hippo."},{"time":973000,"text":"H is for habitat destruction, including climate change forced by greenhouse gases."},{"time":980000,"text":"I is for the invasive species like the fire ants, the zebra mussels, broom grasses"},{"time":988000,"text":"and pathogenic bacteria and viruses that are flooding every country, and at an exponential rate -- that's the I."},{"time":999000,"text":"The P, the first one in \"HIPPO,\" is for pollution."},{"time":1003000,"text":"The second is for continued population, human population expansion."},{"time":1009000,"text":"And the final letter is O, for over-harvesting --"},{"time":1012000,"text":"driving species into extinction by excessive hunting and fishing."},{"time":1016000,"text":"The HIPPO juggernaut we have created, if unabated, is destined --"},{"time":1022000,"text":"according to the best estimates of ongoing biodiversity research --"},{"time":1026000,"text":"to reduce half of Earth's still surviving animal and plant species"},{"time":1031000,"text":"to extinction or critical endangerment by the end of the century."},{"time":1036000,"text":"Human-forced climate change alone -- again, if unabated --"},{"time":1041000,"text":"could eliminate a quarter of surviving species during the next five decades."},{"time":1047000,"text":"What will we and all future generations lose"},{"time":1051000,"text":"if much of the living environment is thus degraded?"},{"time":1057000,"text":"Huge potential sources of scientific information yet to be gathered,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"much of our environmental stability"},{"time":1065000,"text":"and new kinds of pharmaceuticals and new products of unimaginable strength and value --"},{"time":1072000,"text":"all thrown away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075000,"text":"The loss will inflict a heavy price"},{"time":1078000,"text":"in wealth, security and yes, spirituality for all time to come,"},{"time":1085000,"text":"because previous cataclysms of this kind --"},{"time":1087000,"text":"the last one, that ended the age of dinosaurs --"},{"time":1090000,"text":"took, normally, five to 10 million years to repair."},{"time":1096000,"text":"Sadly, our knowledge of biodiversity is so incomplete"},{"time":1100000,"text":"that we are at risk of losing a great deal of it before it is even discovered."},{"time":1105000,"text":"For example, even in the United States, the 200,000 species known currently"},{"time":1114000,"text":"actually has been found to be only partial in coverage;"},{"time":1121000,"text":"it is mostly unknown to us in basic biology."},{"time":1126000,"text":"Only about 15 percent of the known species have been studied well enough to evaluate their status."},{"time":1133000,"text":"Of the 15 percent evaluated, 20 percent are classified as \"in peril,\""},{"time":1139000,"text":"that is, in danger of extinction."},{"time":1141000,"text":"That's in the United States."},{"time":1143000,"text":"We are, in short, flying blind into our environmental future."},{"time":1150000,"text":"We urgently need to change this."},{"time":1152000,"text":"We need to have the biosphere properly explored"},{"time":1156000,"text":"so that we can understand and competently manage it."},{"time":1160000,"text":"We need to settle down before we wreck the planet."},{"time":1164000,"text":"And we need that knowledge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1165000,"text":"This should be a big science project equivalent to the Human Genome Project."},{"time":1170000,"text":"It should be thought of as a biological moonshot with a timetable."},{"time":1175000,"text":"So this brings me to my wish for TEDsters,"},{"time":1179000,"text":"and to anyone else around the world who hears this talk."},{"time":1182000,"text":"I wish we will work together to help create the key tools"},{"time":1188000,"text":"that we need to inspire preservation of Earth's biodiversity."},{"time":1192000,"text":"And let us call it the \"Encyclopedia of Life.\""},{"time":1196000,"text":"What is the \"Encyclopedia of Life?\" A concept that has already taken hold"},{"time":1200000,"text":"and is beginning to spread and be looked at seriously?"},{"time":1204000,"text":"It is an encyclopedia that lives on the Internet"},{"time":1207000,"text":"and is contributed to by thousands of scientists around the world."},{"time":1212000,"text":"Amateurs can do it also."},{"time":1215000,"text":"It has an indefinitely expandable page for each species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1220000,"text":"It makes all key information about life on Earth accessible to anyone,"},{"time":1226000,"text":"on demand, anywhere in the world."},{"time":1228000,"text":"I've written about this idea before,"},{"time":1232000,"text":"and I know there are people in this room who have expended significant effort on it in the past."},{"time":1239000,"text":"But what excites me is that since I first put forward this particular idea in that form,"},{"time":1247000,"text":"science has advanced."},{"time":1249000,"text":"Technology has moved forward."},{"time":1252000,"text":"Today, the practicalities of making such an encyclopedia,"},{"time":1256000,"text":"regardless of the magnitude of the information put into it, are within reach."},{"time":1262000,"text":"Indeed, in the past year, a group of influential scientific institutions"},{"time":1266000,"text":"have begun mobilizing to realize this dream."},{"time":1270000,"text":"I wish you would help them."},{"time":1273000,"text":"Working together, we can make this real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1277000,"text":"The encyclopedia will quickly pay for itself in practical applications."},{"time":1282000,"text":"It will address transcendent qualities in the human consciousness, and sense of human need."},{"time":1288000,"text":"It will transform the science of biology in ways of obvious benefit to humanity."},{"time":1294000,"text":"And most of all, it can inspire a new generation of biologists"},{"time":1299000,"text":"to continue the quest that started, for me personally, 60 years ago:"},{"time":1304000,"text":"to search for life, to understand it and finally, above all, to preserve it."},{"time":1309000,"text":"That is my wish. Thank you."}]}]}